I still remember that morning like it was yesterday. Was in the middle of an English test when the news came in via a hushed whisper to our teacher. And even though I knew something  was off the teacher wouldn't tell me what until everyone finished the test. Longest few minutes of my life.

We turned on the TV afterwards and were in conversation about if it was an accident or not when the 2nd plane hit the south tower and I remember that moment with perfect clarity even after all those years. We went from loud speculation and murmuring to dead silence for a good twenty seconds.

Even at the age of 14 and 15 we all knew that the whole world had changed. We just didn't know how yet.

