I was born in the year 2000, and I'm not all that American to begin with.

But I can say that, I know that events like this- These events need to be taken with caution, and as much as I know little of the pain and grief that anyone that has been involved with something like this, I am sensitive to their grief. That being said, this isn't a spectacular article. But it's also1 not a badly-done one. This is a great article. Admittedly, I didn't think you could pull something as sensitive as 9/11 off I had my doubts.

Yet, I enjoyed this article.

This isn't an SCP that's meant to inspire the reader to be blown away with the sheer amount of awesome with how large of a scale it is.

This isn't an SCP that's poorly-done in a way that leaves the reader with a sense of anger or disappointment at how it was made.

This is a well-thought out, well-meaning, and well-executed article that doesn't really blow anyone away, but just leaves you away with an article that's just poignant and good enough, to muster an upvote.

And for that reason alone, is why this is such a great and superb article.

+1

