I went through three stages of my feelings towards this article. At first I did not like it because it’s hard, maybe impossible for me to fully divorce my feelings about the event and the political situations/ramifications surrounding 9/11/01. For reasons best articulated above by ModernMajorGeneral, I’ve grown tired and cynical over the last seventeen years of yearly tributes that feel hollow and disingenuous. However, this article was neither hollow nor disingenuous, the story and characters were believable and by the end I felt emotional for them. I would upvote any other article with the same qualities, and I think all my negative feelings come from external, real-world sources and not the piece itself. +1 from me







